25|$|The Beinecke Rare Book & Manuscript Library at Yale University {{holds the}} {{majority}} of Edwards' surviving manuscripts, including over one thousand sermons, notebooks, correspondence, printed materials, and artifacts. Two of Edwards' manuscript sermons, a 1737 letter to Mrs. Hannah Morse, and some original minutes of <b>a</b> <b>town</b> <b>meeting</b> in Northampton are held by The Presbyterian Historical Society in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania.|$|E
25|$|In lieu of <b>a</b> <b>town</b> <b>meeting,</b> the Einwohnerrat (residents' council) has {{represented}} {{the wishes of}} its electorate since 1965. The council is composed of 50 members and is empowered to authorize all decisions relevant to the town’s tax rate, budget, annual report, and credit. It can also pass regulations. All members of the council are chosen for four-year terms through a proportional-representation-based electoral process.|$|E
